SummaryInformation_df1: {"Definition": "A rare primary bone dysplasia characterized by the association of multiple epiphyseal dysplasia with macrocephaly and dysmorphic facial features (such as frontal bossing, hypertelorism, flat malar region, low-set ears, and short neck). Patients are of normal stature and present with joint swelling and genu valgum. Additional reported manifestations include clinodactyly, spindle-shaped fingers, and pectus excavatum."}

SummaryInformation_df1: {"Definition": "A rare neurodegenerative disorder of the astrocytes comprised of two clinical forms: Alexander disease (AxD) type I and type II manifesting with various degrees of macrocephaly, spasticity, ataxia and seizures and leading to psychomotor regression and death."}
